==German==
===Etymology===
A shortened form of the Catholic, South German and Austrian first name ''[[Ignatius]]'' (pronounced: /ɪgˈnaːtsiːˌʊs/). Came to mean ''[[Nationalsozialist]]'' ([[National Socialist]]) probably influenced by Hitler's Austrian origin as well as appearance of syllables ''na'' (pronounced: /naː/) and ''zi'' (pronounced: ''tsiː'') in Na''zionalso''zi''alist''.

===Noun===
'''Nazi''' ''m'' (genitive singular: '''[[Nazis]]''', nominative plural: '''[[Nazis]]''')

#a [[member]] or ([[ideological]]) [[supporter]] of the [[NSDAP]] or [[Nazism]]; a [[National Socialist]]
#[A general, extremely strong insult]
#[When used attributively, used to express strong contempt, as [[Nazi-Schwein]], [[Nazi-Journalismus]], etc.]
#[[pet name]] for ''[[Ignatius#German|Ignatius]]''

